article.description: — Zion Griffin's 23 points helped Tennessee State defeat South Carolina State 80-61 on Saturday.
article.headline: Griffin's 23 lead Tennessee State over South Carolina State
article.linkText: Griffin's 23 lead Tennessee State over South Carolina State
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- — Zion Griffin's 23 points helped Tennessee State defeat South Carolina State 80-61 on Saturday. Griffin also had nine rebounds and four blocks for the Tigers (2-0). Jr. Clay scored 23 points, going 7 of 13 from the floor, including 3 for 7 from distance, and 6 for 8 from the line. Marcus Fitzgerald Jr. shot 4 for 11, including 2 for 3 from beyond the arc to finish with 12 points. Lesown Hallums finished with 14 points and three steals for the Bulldogs (0-2). Davion Everett added 11 points and eight rebounds for South Carolina State. Cam Jones had 11 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
